		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2011-07-23T18:35:39+00:00">July 23, 2011 at 6:35 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Holy Shmoly! Many thanks Otto. If your web server is Nginx, you will also need to add a virtual host and symlink for the domain you are mapping; did so by copying the main site&#8217;s virtual host and only changing the &#8216;server name&#8217; to the mapped domain while keeping all the other bits intact. Restarted nginx and was good to go.</p>
<p>Cheers</p>
</div>

