		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2011-10-04T10:43:45+00:00">October 4, 2011 at 10:43 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>No, domain mapping is for use on a Network Installation. This is one install of WP running multiple sites. One wp-config.php file.</p>
<p>I don&#8217;t understand why you&#8217;re trying to change the table prefix. That has nothing to do with it. </p>
<p>Do you have a Network Admin page or don&#8217;t you? If you do, then that&#8217;s all you need. Domain Mapping happens entirely within WP, it doesn&#8217;t need config file changes.</p>
</div>

	<div class="reply">
