	<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6d0ff05b0b0e5a249abb8329dd0f7aa8?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name"><a itemprop='url' href='http://paksatire.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Touseef Ikram</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2010/wordpress-3-0-multisite-domain-mapping-tutorial/comment-page-9/#comment-10008">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2011-10-22T13:09:14+00:00">October 22, 2011 at 1:09 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Thanks Tony for your reply. I am on a dedicated server and have around 25 sites (with their cpanel accounts) on it. Among them there are 5 sites which are running wordpress and I wanted to consolidate them to a single multisite. </p>
<p>Multisite is setup on a new domain with sub-folder installation. All the data has been imported to the sub-folder sites from main sites. I have taken all the steps but the domain still points to the existing accounts and I can not create A/Cname record the way it is described.</p>
