	<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0994d5e2e158a24ba8017c2525d78263?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name"><a itemprop='url' href='http://ottodestruct.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Otto</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2010/wordpress-3-0-multisite-domain-mapping-tutorial/comment-page-9/#comment-9989">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2011-10-21T13:06:35+00:00">October 21, 2011 at 1:06 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Normal posts on the &#8220;root&#8221; domain in a multisite setup gets /blog/ prepended to it&#8217;s single post URLs.</p>
<p>So if your root site is example.com, then its posts will look like <a href="http://example.com/blog/whatever/" rel="nofollow">http://example.com/blog/whatever/</a>. </p>
<p>The &#8220;sub&#8221; sites don&#8217;t get this unless they want it. But the root has to have a distinguishing mark.</p>
</div>

